-$630 is likely embedded\nin an ISM cavity with internal density $n = 0.0010^{+0.0005}_{-0.0003}$\ncm$^{-3}$ and radius $R_{\\rm c} = 0.61^{+0.11}_{-0.09}$ pc, which could have\nbeen produced by the system's previous activity, as proposed for other BH\nLMXBs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Feb 2022 10:52:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-16"}
